        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-25T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.6354/3–2047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Bolivia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-25T16:00:00-05:00">March 25, 1947—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1320. For Bugbee<note n="17" xml:id="d283fn1">Howard C. Bugbee, Attaché at the
                        Embassy in Bolivia.</note> from Karl Anderson.<note n="18" xml:id="d283fn2">Karl L. Anderson, Assistant Chief, International Resources Division.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1748, 20th.<note n="19" xml:id="d283fn3">Not printed.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_RFC1">RFC</gloss> made offer March 21, purchase 15,000 tons
                        <gloss target="#t_Bol1">Bol</gloss> tin to end this year at 76 cents.</p>
                <p>Three weeks ago <gloss target="#t_RFC1">RFC</gloss> offered price 74 cents. Since
                    then <gloss target="#t_Bol1">Bol</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_Arg1">Arg</gloss>
                    trade agreement signed whereby latter agrees purchase for 5 years minimum, 8,000
                    tons <gloss target="#t_Bol1">Bol</gloss> tin annually and additional 12,000 tons
                    annually if free from other contracts at price 76 cents for 1947.</p>
                <p>After receipt latest <gloss target="#t_RFC1">RFC</gloss> offer 76 cents <gloss target="#t_Bol1">Bol</gloss> states impossible sell US more than 11 or
                    12,000 tons since cannot reduce <gloss target="#t_Arg1">Arg</gloss> commitment
                    below 8,000 tons. [Anderson.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
